   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">Both SCP and FTP can be enabled from the command line interface
or the web interface. For information on how see each section:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <xref href="#./Enable_SCP_CLI"
                        scope="local"
                        type="section"
                        class="- topic/xref "/>
               </p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <xref href="#./Enable_FTP_CLI"
                        scope="local"
                        type="section"
                        class="- topic/xref "/>
               </p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <xref href="#./Enable_SCP_GUI"
                        scope="local"
                        type="section"
                        class="- topic/xref "/>
               </p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <xref href="#./Enable_FTP_GUI"
                        scope="local"
                        type="section"
                        class="- topic/xref "/>
               </p>
            </li>
         </ul>
      </p>
      <section id="Enable_SCP_CLI" class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Enable SCP from the CLI</title>
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">To enable SCP, SSH needs to be enable and FTP needs
to be disabled.</p>
            <ol class="- topic/ol ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Log in to the CLI.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">To disable FTP type <codeph translate="no" class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">ftp –s disable</codeph> and press <uicontrol translate="no" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Enter</uicontrol> to confirm.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">To enable SSH type <codeph translate="no" class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">ssh –s enable</codeph> and press <uicontrol translate="no" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Enter</uicontrol> to confirm.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">To set the SSH port, to for example 5000, type <codeph translate="no" class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">ssh –p 5000</codeph>. Available ports are 22,
5000-32768.</p>
                  <note class="- topic/note ">Use a specified SSH port, instead of the default,
to increase security. </note>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">SCP is now enabled.</p>
                  <note conref="Configure_from_the_CLI_CPT_0000354856.dita#ConfigureFromTheCLI-8010148F/Reboot-the-NMC-from-the-CLI-77BE4F3B"
                        class="- topic/note ">A reboot of the NMC might be necessary to activate changes.</note>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </sectiondiv>
      </section>
      <section id="Enable_FTP_CLI" class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Enable FTP from the CLI</title>
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <ol class="- topic/ol ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Log in to the CLI.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">To enable FTP type <codeph translate="no" class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">ftp –s enable</codeph> and press <uicontrol translate="no" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Enter</uicontrol> to confirm.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">To set the FTP port to, for example 5001, type <codeph translate="no" class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">ftp –p 5001</codeph>. Available ports are 21,
5001-32768.</p>
                  <note class="- topic/note ">Use a specified FTP port, instead of the default,
to increase security. </note>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">FTP is now enabled.</p>
                  <note conref="Configure_from_the_CLI_CPT_0000354856.dita#ConfigureFromTheCLI-8010148F/Reboot-the-NMC-from-the-CLI-77BE4F3B"
                        class="- topic/note ">A reboot of the NMC might be necessary to activate changes.</note>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </sectiondiv>
      </section>
      <section id="Enable_SCP_GUI" class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Enable SCP from the Web Interface</title>
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">To enable SCP, SSH needs to be enable and FTP needs
to be disabled.</p>
            <ol class="- topic/ol ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Log in to the web interface.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Navigate to <uicontrol translate="no" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Configuration &gt; Network
&gt; Console &gt; Access</uicontrol>. </p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Check the SSH enable box. It is also possible to specify an
SSH port. Click <uicontrol translate="no" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Apply</uicontrol> to save
the changes.<note class="- topic/note ">Use a specified SSH port, instead of the default,
to increase security. </note>
                     <image href="../Images/NMC_Configuration_Network_Console_Access_0000338179.png"
                            placement="inline"
                            class="- topic/image "/>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Navigate to <uicontrol translate="no" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Configuration &gt; Network
&gt; FTP server</uicontrol>.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Make sure that the FTP enable box is unchecked. Click <uicontrol translate="no" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Apply</uicontrol> to save the changes.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">SCP is now enabled.</p>
                  <note conref="../Library/Reference_Library_CPT_0000338844.dita#Reference_Library-69E2C789/restart_to_apply_change"
                        class="- topic/note ">A reboot of the NMC might be necessary to activate changes.</note>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </sectiondiv>
      </section>
      <section id="Enable_FTP_GUI" class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Enable FTP from the Web Interface</title>
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Log in to the web interface.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Navigate to <uicontrol translate="no" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Configuration &gt; Network
&gt; FTP server</uicontrol>.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Check the FTP enable box. It is also possible to specify an
FTP port. Click <uicontrol translate="no" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Apply</uicontrol> to save
the changes. <note class="- topic/note ">Use a specified FTP port, instead of the default,
to increase security. </note>
                     </p>
                     <image href="../Images/NMC_Configuration_Network_FTP-server_0000338180.png"
                            placement="inline"
                            class="- topic/image "/>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">FTP is now enabled.</p>
                     <note conref="../Library/Reference_Library_CPT_0000338844.dita#Reference_Library-69E2C789/restart_to_apply_change"
                           class="- topic/note ">A reboot of the NMC might be necessary to activate changes.</note>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </p>
         </sectiondiv>
      </section>
